The paper is about learning-to-rank for information retrieval, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) in computer science. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a neural learning-to-rank model that employs a self-attention mechanism, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), suggesting that cs.CL and cs.CV are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions that the proposed model achieves state-of-the-art performance, indicating that it may be related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), which are covered by cs.LG and cs.AI, respectively.
